      h1 Adventures in Markdown-To-HTML
      h2 19 Dec 2019
      h3 Promises galore!
      p In creating this portfolio/resume/personal website, I thought it might be nice to have a system where I could just write a series of individual, self-contained posts in markdown format, and then translate that document to #[a(href="https://pugjs.org/api/getting-started.html") pug]. It turned out to be a little bit more involved than that, since then generation didn’t account for things like links inside of paragraphs or fenced code blocks. There was also plenty of async/await going on behind the scenes in order to make sure that the page didn’t render before the conversion took place.
      p There’s also the possibility that I over-thought/ over-engineered the whole thing and made a real SNAFU of a possibly simplistic matter. But at the time, this seemed to be the most elegant way to achieve what I wanted to do.
      h4 Lets start from the top…
